sign.md ---\n254: # Session Store — Design\n255: \n256: ## Module\n257: \n258: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n259: \n260: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n261: \n262: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n263: \n264: ```go\n265: package store\n266: \n267: import (\n268:     \"context\"\n269:     \"time\"\n270: \n271:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n272: )\n273: \n274: type Store interface {\n275:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n276:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n277:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n278:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n279:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n280:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n281:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n282:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n283:     Close() error\n284: }\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### Errors\n288: \n289: ```go\n290: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n294: \n295: ```go\n296: const (\n297:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n298:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n299: )\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### Singleton\n303: \n304: ```go\n305: var (\n306:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n307:     provider      Store\n308: )\n309: \n310: func Storage() Store\n311: func initStore() error\n312: ```\n313: \n314: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n315: \n316: ### Sandbox document type\n317: \n318: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n319: \n320: ```go\n321: type SandboxInfo struct {\n322:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n323:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n324:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n325:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n326:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n327:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n328:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n329:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n330:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n331: }\n332: \n333: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n334:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n335:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n336:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n337: }\n338: ```\n339: \n340: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n341: \n342: ### Struct\n343: \n344: ```go\n345: type redisStore struct {\n346:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n347:     sessionPrefix        string\n348:     expiryIndexKey       string\n349:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n350: }\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Fixed key patterns\n354: \n355: | Field | Value |\n356: |-------|--------|\n357: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n358: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n359: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n360: \n361: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n362: \n363: ```go\n364: return &redisv9.Options{\n365:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n366:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n367: }, nil\n368: ```\n369: \n370: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n371: \n372: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n373: |----------|----------|--------|\n374: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n375: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n376: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n377: \n378: ### Operations summary\n379: \n380: | Method | Redis commands |\n381: |--------|----------------|\n382: | `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n383: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n384: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n385: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n386: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n387: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n388: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n389: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n390: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n391: \n392: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n393: - `sessionKey(id)` → `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n394: \n395: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n396: \n397: ### Struct\n398: \n399: ```go\n400: type valkeyStore struct {\n401:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n402:     sessionPrefix        string\n403:     expiryIndexKey       string\n404:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n405: }\n406: ```\n407: \n408: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n409: \n410: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n411: \n412: ```go\n413: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n414:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n415:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n416: }\n417: ```\n418: \n419: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n420: \n421: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n422: \n423: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n424: |----------|----------|--------|\n425: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list → `InitAddress` |\n426: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n427: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n428: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n429: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n430: \n431: ### Operations summary\n432: \n433: | Method | Valkey API |\n434: |--------|------------|\n435: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n436: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n437: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n438: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n439: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n440: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n441: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n442: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n443: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n444: \n445: ### ZSET score semantics\n446: \n447: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n448: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n449: \n450: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n451: \n452: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n453: \n454: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n455: \n456: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n457: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n458: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n459: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n460: \n461: \n462: --- session-store/spec.md ---\n463: # Session Store Specification\n464: \n465: ## Purpose\n466: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n467: \n468: ## Requirements\n469: \n470: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n471: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n474: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n475: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n476: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n477: \n478: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n479: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n482: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n483: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n484: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n485: \n486: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n487: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: Key construction\n490: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n491: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n492: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n493: \n494: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n495: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n498: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n499: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n500: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n501: \n502: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n503: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n504: \n505: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n506: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n507: - **WHEN** executed\n508: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n509: \n510: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n511: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n514: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n515: - **WHEN** called\n516: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n517: \n518: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n519: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n522: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n523: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n524: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n525: \n526: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n527: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: Full removal\n530: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n531: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n532: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n533: \n534: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n535: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n538: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n539: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n540: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n541: \n542: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n543: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n544: \n545: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n546: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n547: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n548: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n549: \n550: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n551: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n552: \n553: #### Scenario: Default redis\n554: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n555: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n556: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n557: \n558: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n559: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n560: \n561: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n562: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n563: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n564: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n565: \n566: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n567: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n568: \n569: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n570: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n571: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n572: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n573: \n574: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n575: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n576: \n577: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n578: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n579: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n580: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n581: \n582: \n583: Use OpenSpec format. Each requirement must have acceptance scenarios.\n\n(End of file - total 583 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Write delta-spec.md (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios) for the agentcube project:\n\nAR: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\nModule: pkg/store\nLanguage: Go\nSize: S\n\nBase specs:\n--- deployment/client-go.md ---\n# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775864269199,"end":1775864269224}}}}
