{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775864278903,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c26f74001S4H1qfElpOf5yO","messageID":"msg_d79c26979001m8sfGFGVHtH0wO","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864283993,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c27b91001F8WxGDtp7yXG5F","messageID":"msg_d79c26979001m8sfGFGVHtH0wO","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n9: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n12: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n13: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n14: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n17: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n20: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n21: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n22: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n25: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Key construction\n28: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n29: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n30: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n33: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n36: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n37: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n38: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n41: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n44: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n45: - **WHEN** executed\n46: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n49: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n52: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n53: - **WHEN** called\n54: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n57: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n60: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n61: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n62: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n65: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Full removal\n68: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n69: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n70: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n73: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n76: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n77: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n78: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n81: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n84: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n85: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n86: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n89: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Default redis\n92: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n93: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n94: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n97: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n100: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n101: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n102: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n105: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n108: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n109: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n110: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n113: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n116: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n117: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n118: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store Specification\n\n## Purpose\nPersist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n### Requirement: Not found semantics\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/spec.md","time":{"start":1775864283978,"end":1775864283991}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864283994,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c27fb0001kSOM2Q4j4cQit1","messageID":"msg_d79c26979001m8sfGFGVHtH0wO","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n8: \n9: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: package store\n13: \n14: import (\n15:     \"context\"\n16:     \"time\"\n17: \n18:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n19: )\n20: \n21: type Store interface {\n22:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n23:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n24:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n25:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n26:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n27:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n28:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n29:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n30:     Close() error\n31: }\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Errors\n35: \n36: ```go\n37: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n41: \n42: ```go\n43: const (\n44:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n45:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n46: )\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Singleton\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: var (\n53:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n54:     provider      Store\n55: )\n56: \n57: func Storage() Store\n58: func initStore() error\n59: ```\n60: \n61: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n62: \n63: ### Sandbox document type\n64: \n65: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: type SandboxInfo struct {\n69:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n70:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n71:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n72:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n73:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n74:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n75:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n76:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n77:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n78: }\n79: \n80: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n81:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n82:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n83:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n88: \n89: ### Struct\n90: \n91: ```go\n92: type redisStore struct {\n93:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n94:     sessionPrefix        string\n95:     expiryIndexKey       string\n96:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Fixed key patterns\n101: \n102: | Field | Value |\n103: |-------|--------|\n104: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n105: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n106: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n107: \n108: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: return &redisv9.Options{\n112:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n113:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n114: }, nil\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n118: \n119: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n120: |----------|----------|--------|\n121: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n122: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n123: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n124: \n125: ### Operations summary\n126: \n127: | Method | Redis commands |\n128: |--------|----------------|\n129: | `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n130: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n131: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n132: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n133: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n134: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n135: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n136: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n137: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n138: \n139: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n140: - `sessionKey(id)` → `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n141: \n142: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n143: \n144: ### Struct\n145: \n146: ```go\n147: type valkeyStore struct {\n148:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n149:     sessionPrefix        string\n150:     expiryIndexKey       string\n151:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n156: \n157: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n161:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n162:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n167: \n168: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n169: \n170: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n171: |----------|----------|--------|\n172: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list → `InitAddress` |\n173: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n174: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n175: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n176: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n177: \n178: ### Operations summary\n179: \n180: | Method | Valkey API |\n181: |--------|------------|\n182: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n183: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n184: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n185: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n186: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n187: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n188: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n189: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n190: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n191: \n192: ### ZSET score semantics\n193: \n194: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n195: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n196: \n197: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n198: \n199: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n200: \n201: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n202: \n203: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n204: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n205: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n206: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n### Store interface (exact signatures)\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/design.md","time":{"start":1775864283980,"end":1775864283993}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864283997,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c27739001X1NwEpG1R752Yg","messageID":"msg_d79c26979001m8sfGFGVHtH0wO","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Changes to pkg/store\n4: \n5: (TBD - Delta specification to be completed)\n6: \n7: ## Interface Definitions\n8: \n9: (TBD)\n10: \n11: ## Type Definitions\n12: \n13: (TBD)\n14: \n15: ## Constants\n16: \n17: (TBD)\n\n(End of file - total 17 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 Delta Spec\n\n## Changes to pkg/store\n\n(TBD - Delta specification to be completed)\n\n## Interface Definitions\n\n(TBD)\n\n## Type Definitions\n\n(TBD)\n\n## Constants\n\n(TBD)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864283974,"end":1775864283995}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775864284023,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c2835d001Xo1kZuwomJLrib","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79c26979001m8sfGFGVHtH0wO","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":26607,"input":4,"output":258,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":5077,"read":21268}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775864288164,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c293a1001EbajEqwt15hOCG","messageID":"msg_d79c2838b001j9tRIh60NqEnip","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864292035,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c29cbc001l9Vs83YqqQGIDM","messageID":"msg_d79c2838b001j9tRIh60NqEnip","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-011  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [pkg/router/jwt.go](../../pkg/router/jwt.go)\n10: \n11: The Router JWT Authentication and Issuance component provides RSA-based JWT token generation, signing, and key management for the AgentCube router. It enables secure authentication between the router and the Workload Manager by generating signed JWT tokens with session-specific claims, while persisting RSA key pairs in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: RSA Key Pair Generation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL generate cryptographically secure RSA key pairs for JWT signing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Generate new RSA key pair on initialization\n22: - **GIVEN** a fresh router instance starting without existing keys\n23: - **WHEN** `NewJWTManager()` is called\n24: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a 2048-bit RSA key pair\n25: - **AND** return a `JWTManager` with the private and public keys initialized\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: RSA key generation uses secure random source\n28: - **GIVEN** the router requires a new JWT signing key\n29: - **WHEN** the RSA key is generated using `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n30: - **THEN** the key SHALL be generated using cryptographically secure random source\n31: - **AND** the private key SHALL be suitable for RS256 signing\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Handle RSA generation failure\n34: - **GIVEN** the system is unable to generate RSA keys due to resource constraints\n35: - **WHEN** `NewJWTManager()` is called and key generation fails\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to generate RSA key\"\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: JWT Token Generation and Signing\n41: \n42: The system SHALL generate and sign JWT tokens with configurable claims using RS256 algorithm.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Generate token with custom claims\n45: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with valid RSA keys\n46: - **AND** a claims map containing `{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"sess-abc-123\\\", \\\"user\\\": \\\"test-user\\\"}`\n47: - **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a signed JWT string containing all custom claims\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: JWT includes standard claims automatically\n51: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with valid RSA keys\n52: - **WHEN** any token is generated via `GenerateToken()`\n53: - **THEN** the token SHALL include the following standard claims:\n54:   - `exp`: expiration time (current time + 5 minutes)\n55:   - `iat`: issued at time (current timestamp)\n56:   - `iss`: issuer (\"agentcube-router\")\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: JWT uses RS256 signing algorithm\n59: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with RSA private key\n60: - **WHEN** `GenerateToken()` is called with any claims\n61: - **THEN** the token SHALL be signed using `jwt.SigningMethodRS256`\n62: - **AND** the signature SHALL be verifiable with the corresponding public key\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Handle signing failure\n65: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with corrupted or invalid private key\n66: - **WHEN** `GenerateToken()` is called\n67: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to sign token\"\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Token expiration is configurable via claims override\n70: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with valid keys\n71: - **AND** a claims map containing a custom `exp` value\n72: - **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called\n73: - **THEN** the custom expiration SHALL override the default 5-minute expiration\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: RSA Key PEM Encoding\n78: \n79: The system SHALL provide methods to export RSA keys in standard PEM format.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Export public key in PEM format\n82: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with an RSA key pair\n83: - **WHEN** `GetPublicKeyPEM()` is called\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the public key encoded as PKIX PEM format\n85: - **AND** the PEM block type SHALL be \"PUBLIC KEY\"\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Export private key in PEM format\n88: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with an RSA key pair\n89: - **WHEN** `GetPrivateKeyPEM()` is called\n90: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the private key encoded as PKCS#1 PEM format\n91: - **AND** the PEM block type SHALL be \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: PEM encoding for key storage\n94: - **GIVEN** keys need to be stored in Kubernetes Secrets\n95: - **WHEN** `GetPublicKeyPEM()` and `GetPrivateKeyPEM()` are called\n96: - **THEN** the returned byte slices SHALL be valid UTF-8 strings\n97: - **AND** they SHALL be parseable by standard PEM decoders\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Secret Key Storage\n102: \n103: The system SHALL persist and retrieve RSA keys from Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide access.\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Create new secret when none exists\n106: - **GIVEN** the router is running in a Kubernetes cluster\n107: - **AND** no secret named `picod-router-identity` exists in the configured namespace\n108: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n109: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new Secret with:\n110:   - Name: `picod-router-identity`\n111:   - Namespace: `$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (or \"default\")\n112:   - Labels: `app=agentcube`, `component=router`\n113:   - Data keys: `private.pem`, `public.pem`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Load existing keys from secret\n116: - **GIVEN** a secret `picod-router-identity` already exists in the namespace\n117: - **AND** the secret contains valid `private.pem` and `public.pem` data\n118: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the existing keys into the `JWTManager`\n120: - **AND** the loaded keys SHALL replace the ephemeral keys\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Handle non-cluster environment gracefully\n123: - **GIVEN** the router is NOT running in a Kubernetes cluster\n124: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n125: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning message\n126: - **AND** return nil (no error) to continue with ephemeral keys\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Handle Kubernetes client creation failure\n129: - **GIVEN** the router is running in-cluster but cannot create Kubernetes client\n130: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` attempts to create the clientset\n131: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to create Kubernetes client\"\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Handle secret creation failure\n134: - **GIVEN** the router has valid Kubernetes client\n135: - **AND** secret creation fails for reasons other than AlreadyExists\n136: - **WHEN** attempting to create the JWT secret\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to create JWT secret\"\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Handle malformed key data in existing secret\n140: - **GIVEN** an existing secret with invalid or corrupted `private.pem` data\n141: - **WHEN** `loadExistingSecret()` attempts to parse the key\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating key parsing failure\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: JWT Key Loading from PEM\n147: \n148: The system SHALL be able to parse and load RSA private keys from PEM-encoded data.\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Load private key from valid PEM data\n151: - **GIVEN** valid PKCS#1 RSA private key PEM data\n152: - **WHEN** `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` is called with the PEM bytes\n153: - **THEN** the system SHALL parse and set the private key\n154: - **AND** derive and set the corresponding public key\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Handle invalid PEM block\n157: - **GIVEN** PEM data that cannot be decoded\n158: - **WHEN** `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` is called\n159: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to decode PEM block\"\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Handle invalid PKCS#1 key data\n162: - **GIVEN** PEM data with valid structure but invalid key content\n163: - **WHEN** `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` attempts to parse the key\n164: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to parse private key\"\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: Namespace Configuration\n169: \n170: The system SHALL support configurable namespace for JWT secret storage.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Default namespace is \"default\"\n173: - **GIVEN** the `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable is not set\n174: - **WHEN** the router package is initialized\n175: - **THEN** `IdentityNamespace` SHALL default to \"default\"\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Namespace from environment variable\n178: - **GIVEN** the `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable is set to \"agentcube-system\"\n179: - **WHEN** the router package is initialized\n180: - **THEN** `IdentityNamespace` SHALL be set to \"agentcube-system\"\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Token Validation Support\n185: \n186: The system SHALL provide capabilities to validate JWT tokens using the stored public key.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Validate token signature\n189: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed by the `JWTManager`'s private key\n190: - **AND** the corresponding public key is available\n191: - **WHEN** the token is validated using the public key\n192: - **THEN** the signature SHALL be verified successfully\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Reject token with invalid signature\n195: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with a different key\n196: - **WHEN** validation is attempted with the current public key\n197: - **THEN** the validation SHALL fail with a signature error\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Reject expired token\n200: - **GIVEN** a JWT token that has exceeded its `exp` claim time\n201: - **WHEN** the token is validated\n202: - **THEN** the validation SHALL fail with an expiration error\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Changes to Base Specification\n207: \n208: No modifications to existing interfaces. This AR adds new JWT management capabilities.\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ## New Interfaces\n213: \n214: ### JWTManager\n215: \n216: ```go\n217: // JWTManager handles RSA key generation, JWT token signing, and key persistence.\n218: type JWTManager struct {\n219:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey    // RSA private key for signing\n220:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey     // RSA public key for verification\n221:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface // Kubernetes client for secret operations\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: #### Methods\n226: \n227: | Method | Signature | Description |\n228: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n229: | `NewJWTManager` | `func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)` | Creates new JWTManager with generated RSA key pair |\n230: | `GenerateToken` | `func (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)` | Creates and signs JWT with custom claims |\n231: | `GetPublicKeyPEM` | `func (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)` | Returns public key in PKIX PEM format |\n232: | `GetPrivateKeyPEM` | `func (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)` | Returns private key in PKCS#1 PEM format |\n233: | `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` | `func (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error` | Stores or loads keys from Kubernetes Secret |\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ## Modified Interfaces\n238: \n239: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## Behavioral Changes\n244: \n245: | Behavior | Before | After |\n246: |----------|--------|-------|\n247: | JWT signing | Not supported | RS256-signed JWT with configurable claims |\n248: | Key persistence | Ephemeral only | Kubernetes Secret storage with fallback |\n249: | Key generation | None | 2048-bit RSA key generation on startup |\n250: | Token standard claims | None | exp, iat, iss auto-populated |\n251: | Cross-pod key sharing | Not possible | Via Kubernetes Secret in configured namespace |\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ## Dependencies\n256: \n257: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n258: |------------|---------|---------|\n259: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT token creation and signing |\n260: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n261: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | v0.34.1 | Secret type definitions |\n262: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes metadata types |\n263: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API error handling |\n264: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n265: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard library | RSA key generation |\n266: | `crypto/x509` | Standard library | Key encoding/decoding |\n267: | `encoding/pem` | Standard library | PEM format handling |\n268: | `crypto/rand` | Standard library | Secure random number generation |\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ## File Index\n273: \n274: | Path | Purpose |\n275: |------|---------|\n276: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager implementation with key generation, token signing, and secret storage |\n277: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | JWT-specific error types (`JWTSigningError`) |\n278: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Configuration constants (e.g., `IdentityNamespace` initialization) |\n279: \n280: ---\n281: \n282: ## Constants\n283: \n284: | Constant | Value | Description |\n285: |----------|-------|-------------|\n286: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key bit length |\n287: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | Default token expiration duration |\n288: | `identitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes Secret name for key storage |\n289: | `privateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n290: | `publicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n291: | `IdentityNamespace` | `\"default\"` or `$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Namespace for JWT secret storage |\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## API Endpoints Summary\n296: \n297: This AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n298: \n299: | Consumer | Usage |\n300: |----------|-------|\n301: | SessionManager | JWT tokens for Workload Manager authentication |\n302: | Router Server | Token generation for session claims |\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ## Migration Notes\n307: \n308: - **New dependency**: Add `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` to go.mod\n309: - **RBAC requirement**: Router requires permission to create/get Secrets in the target namespace\n310: - **Secret naming**: Uses `picod-router-identity` Secret name; ensure no conflicts\n311: - **Namespace configuration**: Set `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var for non-default namespace\n312: - **Key rotation**: To rotate keys, delete the `picod-router-identity` Secret; new keys will be generated\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n317: \n318: 1. **Key Generation**: RSA-2048 keys are generated on `NewJWTManager()` with secure random source\n319: 2. **Token Creation**: `GenerateToken()` produces valid RS256-signed JWTs with standard and custom claims\n320: 3. **Key Persistence**: Keys are stored in and loaded from Kubernetes Secret `picod-router-identity`\n321: 4. **PEM Encoding**: Keys can be exported in standard PEM format for external use\n322: 5. **Error Handling**: All failure scenarios return descriptive errors without panicking\n323: 6. **Namespace Support**: Secret namespace is configurable via `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable\n324: 7. **Non-cluster Fallback**: Gracefully handles non-Kubernetes environments with ephemeral keys\n325: 8. **Token Validation**: Generated tokens can be validated using the stored public key\n\n(End of file - total 325 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [pkg/router/jwt.go](../../pkg/router/jwt.go)\n\nThe Router JWT Authentication and Issuance component provides RSA-based JWT token generation, signing, and key management for the AgentCube router. It enables secure authentication between the router and the Workload Manager by generating signed JWT tokens with session-specific claims, while persisting RSA key pairs in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: RSA Key Pair Generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate cryptographically secure RSA key pairs for JWT signing.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864292025,"end":1775864292032}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775864292056,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c2a2c2001TyDc4NowklxIPi","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79c2838b001j9tRIh60NqEnip","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":30989,"input":4,"output":139,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":4501,"read":26345}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775864315921,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c3000f001ETDOaKAc4ePbrc","messageID":"msg_d79c2a2ee001zGg0r3Pc7veqpb","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864319067,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c309bf001azBsjWpDragfEx","messageID":"msg_d79c2a2ee001zGg0r3Pc7veqpb","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write a comprehensive delta-spec.md for AR-012 following the same format as AR-011:","time":{"start":1775864319066,"end":1775864319066}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864613396,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c54c74001iJWAcSvsyuf1ls","messageID":"msg_d79c2a2ee001zGg0r3Pc7veqpb","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"text","text":" sandbox","time":{"start":1775864613393,"end":1775864613393}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864613433,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c30c5c001dmjyy13hGCsYdM","messageID":"msg_d79c2a2ee001zGg0r3Pc7veqpb","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-012  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md), [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Session Store Interface provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. It enables CRUD operations on sandbox information, indexes sessions by expiry and last activity times for garbage collection, and provides a thread-safe singleton access pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods for session management.\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface methods\n- **GIVEN** a `Store` implementation (Redis or Valkey)\n- **WHEN** the interface is used\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide:\n  - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` - verify connectivity\n  - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - retrieve sandbox\n  - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - create new sandbox\n  - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - update existing sandbox\n  - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` - delete sandbox\n  - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list expired\n  - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list inactive\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` - update activity timestamp\n  - `Close() error` - close the store connection\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n- **AND** returns nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Ping fails on unhealthy server\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable or unhealthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when operations target a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` exists in the backend\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"unknown-session\")` is called\n- **THEN** the returned error SHALL be `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** the result SHALL be nil\n\n#### Scenario: Redis nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** a Redis backend\n- **AND** a non-existent session key\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `redis.Nil`\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey backend\n- **AND** a non-existent session key\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `IsValkeyNil` response\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Update activity on missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"missing-id\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify any ZSET indexes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Key Naming\n\nThe system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction for session\n- **GIVEN** a session id `abc123`\n- **WHEN** the store writes or reads sandbox data\n- **THEN** the string key SHALL be `session:abc123`\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction with special characters\n- **GIVEN** a session id containing special characters like `sess-123_test.abc`\n- **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n- **THEN** the key SHALL be `session:sess-123_test.abc`\n- **AND** the session id SHALL be preserved exactly\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Expiry Index Management\n\nThe system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds for garbage collection.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` and `ExpiresAt=time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZADD session:expiry 1234567890 sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from expiry index\n- **GIVEN** an existing session in the expiry index\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n- **AND** `before` timestamp is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n- **THEN** it SHALL select members with scores from negative infinity through `1234567890`\n- **AND** limit results to `limit` entries\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes with limit <= 0 returns empty\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit\n- **WHEN** the method is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying the backend\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes loads full documents\n- **GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids `[\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\"]`\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` continues processing\n- **THEN** it SHALL fetch the full JSON documents for each session id\n- **AND** return a slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Last-Activity Index Management\n\nThe system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to activity index with current time\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** current time is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567890 sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity updates activity index\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** update time `at = time.Unix(1234567900, 0)`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567900 sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity with zero time uses now\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** `at` is zero time (`time.Time{}`)\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `time.Now().Unix()` as the score\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from activity index\n- **GIVEN** an existing session in the activity index\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n- **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n- **AND** `before` timestamp is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **WHEN** executed\n- **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `1234567890` SHALL be returned up to `limit`\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes with limit <= 0 returns empty\n- **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)`\n- **WHEN** the method is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying the backend\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity and Validation\n\nThe system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block.\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis/Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid expiry\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis/Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Empty SessionID rejected\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid session ID\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox to store\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute in a single pipeline/multi:\n  - `SETNX session:{id} {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_at_unix} {id}`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} {id}`\n\n#### Scenario: Pipeline failure returns error\n- **GIVEN** any command in the StoreSandbox pipeline fails\n- **WHEN** execution completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error\n- **AND** partial writes SHALL NOT occur (atomic operation)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n\nThe system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries.\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox modifies only session data\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with updated sandbox info\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute `SET session:{id} {json} XX`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify `session:expiry` ZSET\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify `session:last_activity` ZSET\n\n#### Scenario: Missing key on update returns error\n- **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs on Redis\n- **THEN** SET with XX returns nil\n- **AND** the system SHALL return error `key not exists`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing key on update returns error (Valkey)\n- **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs on Valkey\n- **THEN** if response is not \"OK\"\n- **AND** the system SHALL return error indicating key does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox on update rejected\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n\nThe system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n\n#### Scenario: Full removal cleanup\n- **GIVEN** an existing session `sess-1`\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` succeeds\n- **THEN** `GET session:sess-1` SHALL return not found\n- **AND** `session:expiry` ZSET SHALL NOT contain `sess-1`\n- **AND** `session:last_activity` ZSET SHALL NOT contain `sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete executes in atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** an existing session to delete\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL execute in a single pipeline/multi:\n  - `DEL session:{id}`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry {id}`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity {id}`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session ID returns error\n- **GIVEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid session ID\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: List Loaders Tolerate Missing Keys\n\nWhen listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing without failing the whole batch.\n\n#### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n- **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a corresponding string value\n- **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n- **THEN** that id SHALL be omitted from the returned slice\n- **AND** the operation SHALL continue with other valid sessions\n\n#### Scenario: Redis pipeline GET nil handling\n- **GIVEN** Redis pipeline GET returns nil for some keys\n- **WHEN** processing list results\n- **THEN** nil results SHALL be filtered out\n- **AND** only valid sandbox documents SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey MGET empty string handling\n- **GIVEN** Valkey MGET returns empty string for missing keys\n- **WHEN** processing list results\n- **THEN** empty results SHALL be filtered out\n- **AND** only valid sandbox documents SHALL be returned\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n\nThe system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", now)`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid session ID\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query the backend\n\n#### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"unknown-id\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** after existence check fails\n- **AND** the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT update the activity index\n\n#### Scenario: Zero time defaults to now\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", time.Time{})`\n- **AND** session key exists\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `time.Now().Unix()` as the ZADD score\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Selection via STORE_TYPE\n\nThe system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n\n#### Scenario: Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n- **THEN** the Redis implementation SHALL be constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Case-insensitive Redis selection\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` (uppercase)\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** the Redis implementation SHALL be constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Case-insensitive Valkey selection\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=Valkey` (mixed case)\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** the Valkey implementation SHALL be constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=invalid`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with an error indicating unsupported store type\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Redis Environment and Password Policy\n\nThe system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n\n#### Scenario: Password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating password is required\n\n#### Scenario: Password can be disabled\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL succeed with empty password\n\n#### Scenario: Missing REDIS_ADDR fails\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is not set\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating address is required\n\n#### Scenario: Case-insensitive password required flag\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE`\n- **WHEN** checking password requirement\n- **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as disabled (case-insensitive compare to \"false\")\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Environment and Options\n\nThe system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n\n#### Scenario: Parse comma-separated Valkey addresses\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey1:6379,valkey2:6379,valkey3:6379`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `InitAddress` SHALL be `[\"valkey1:6379\", \"valkey2:6379\", \"valkey3:6379\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: DisableCache when VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` SHALL be true on `ClientOption`\n\n#### Scenario: DisableCache when VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=1\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=1`\n- **WHEN** parsing the option\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` SHALL be true (ParseBool accepts \"1\" as true)\n\n#### Scenario: ForceSingleClient when VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` SHALL be true on `ClientOption`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n- **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating password is required\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Missing VALKEY_ADDR fails\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n- **AND** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **WHEN** store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating address is required\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Singleton Access Pattern\n\nThe system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n\n#### Scenario: Single initialization\n- **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n- **WHEN** they execute\n- **THEN** `initStore` SHALL execute exactly once\n- **AND** all goroutines SHALL receive the same Store instance\n\n#### Scenario: Successful init returns same instance\n- **GIVEN** `Storage()` has been called once successfully\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called again\n- **THEN** the same Store instance SHALL be returned\n- **AND** initialization logic SHALL NOT re-execute\n\n#### Scenario: Failed init logs fatal\n- **GIVEN** store initialization fails (e.g., missing required env var)\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`\n- **AND** the program SHALL terminate\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Store Close Behavior\n\nThe system SHALL properly close store connections and release resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Close releases Redis connection\n- **GIVEN** a Redis store instance with an active connection\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the underlying Redis client SHALL be closed\n- **AND** subsequent operations SHALL fail with connection errors\n\n#### Scenario: Close releases Valkey connection\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey store instance with an active connection\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the underlying Valkey client SHALL be closed\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil on success\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nNo modifications to existing interfaces. This AR introduces new storage capabilities for session management.\n\n---\n\n## New Interfaces\n\n### Store Interface\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\n// Store defines the interface for session storage operations.\ntype Store interface {\n    // Ping verifies connectivity to the storage backend.\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n\n    // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox info by session ID.\n    // Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // StoreSandbox creates a new sandbox entry with atomic index updates.\n    // Validates sandbox is non-nil and has valid ExpiresAt.\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\n    // UpdateSandbox updates an existing sandbox's JSON data.\n    // Uses SET with XX flag (key must exist).\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\n    // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox and its indexes.\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n\n    // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sessions with ExpiresAt <= before.\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sessions with last activity <= before.\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n    // Returns ErrNotFound if session does not exist.\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n\n    // Close closes the store connection.\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Errors\n\n```go\n// ErrNotFound is returned when a session key is not found.\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n### Provider Type Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n    valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n)\n```\n\n### Singleton Access\n\n```go\n// Storage returns the singleton Store instance.\n// Panics via klog.Fatal if initialization fails.\nfunc Storage() Store\n```\n\n---\n\n## Modified Interfaces\n\nNone. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n| Behavior | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Session persistence | Not available | Redis/Valkey backed storage |\n| Expiry tracking | Not available | ZSET index `session:expiry` for GC |\n| Activity tracking | Not available | ZSET index `session:last_activity` for idle detection |\n| Store provider | None | Configurable via `STORE_TYPE` env var |\n| Store access | None | Singleton pattern via `Storage()` |\n| Connection pooling | None | Managed by Redis/Valkey client libraries |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client for Go |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Latest | Valkey client for Go |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo type definition |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface definition and ErrNotFound |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Singleton Storage() access and provider selection |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation of Store interface |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation of Store interface |\n\n---\n\n## Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `redisStoreType` | `\"redis\"` | Redis provider type identifier |\n| `valkeyStoreType` | `\"valkey\"` | Valkey provider type identifier |\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Key prefix for session data |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry tracking |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity tracking |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Store provider: `redis` or `valkey` |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Redis server address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Redis authentication password |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes** | - | Comma-separated Valkey addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes** | - | Valkey authentication password |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client cache |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` for single client mode |\n\n*Required when `STORE_TYPE=redis`  \n**Required when `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\nThis AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager | Persist and retrieve sandbox session metadata |\n| Idle Cleanup | Query inactive/expired sessions for garbage collection |\n| Session Router | Update activity timestamps on session access |\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` and/or `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` to go.mod\n- **Environment setup**: Configure `REDIS_ADDR` or `VALKEY_ADDR` before deployment\n- **RBAC**: No Kubernetes RBAC requirements for this component\n- **Data format**: SandboxInfo is stored as JSON; ensure `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` is stable\n- **Index management**: The store manages ZSET indexes automatically; no manual migration needed\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. **Interface Contract**: All Store methods are implemented for both Redis and Valkey backends\n2. **Key Naming**: Session keys use `session:{id}` format consistently\n3. **Index Management**: Expiry and activity ZSETs are maintained correctly\n4. **Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` is returned for missing sessions; other errors are descriptive\n5. **Atomicity**: StoreSandbox and DeleteSandboxBySessionID use atomic pipeline operations\n6. **Provider Selection**: `STORE_TYPE` correctly selects between Redis and Valkey implementations\n7. **Environment Validation**: Required environment variables are validated at initialization\n8. **Singleton Pattern**: `Storage()` provides thread-safe singleton access\n9. **Resource Cleanup**: `Close()` properly releases backend connections\n10. **Orphan Tolerance**: List operations gracefully handle orphaned ZSET entries\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864613400,"end":1775864613430}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775864613464,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c78a39001NnABWZNjCKXL7t","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79c2a2ee001zGg0r3Pc7veqpb","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":41824,"input":4,"output":6786,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":4188,"read":30846}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775864617594,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c79a77001C6BUWi5N5EHnLQ","messageID":"msg_d79c78a72001xp6LXazNweBrLw","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864619937,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c79dca001pbqqZmvFpAp7Xm","messageID":"msg_d79c78a72001xp6LXazNweBrLw","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"head -100 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","description":"Verify delta-spec.md content"},"output":"# AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-012  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md), [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Session Store Interface provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. It enables CRUD operations on sandbox information, indexes sessions by expiry and last activity times for garbage collection, and provides a thread-safe singleton access pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods for session management.\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface methods\n- **GIVEN** a `Store` implementation (Redis or Valkey)\n- **WHEN** the interface is used\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide:\n  - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` - verify connectivity\n  - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - retrieve sandbox\n  - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - create new sandbox\n  - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - update existing sandbox\n  - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` - delete sandbox\n  - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list expired\n  - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list inactive\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` - update activity timestamp\n  - `Close() error` - close the store connection\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n- **AND** returns nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Ping fails on unhealthy server\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable or unhealthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when operations target a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` exists in the backend\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"unknown-session\")` is called\n- **THEN** the returned error SHALL be `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** the result SHALL be nil\n\n#### Scenario: Redis nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** a Redis backend\n- **AND** a non-existent session key\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `redis.Nil`\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey backend\n- **AND** a non-existent session key\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `IsValkeyNil` response\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Update activity on missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"missing-id\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify any ZSET indexes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Key Naming\n\nThe system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction for session\n- **GIVEN** a session id `abc123`\n- **WHEN** the store writes or reads sandbox data\n- **THEN** the string key SHALL be `session:abc123`\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction with special characters\n- **GIVEN** a session id containing special characters like `sess-123_test.abc`\n- **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n- **THEN** the key SHALL be `session:sess-123_test.abc`\n- **AND** the session id SHALL be preserved exactly\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Expiry Index Management\n\nThe system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds for garbage collection.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` and `ExpiresAt=time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n","metadata":{"output":"# AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-012  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md), [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Session Store Interface provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. It enables CRUD operations on sandbox information, indexes sessions by expiry and last activity times for garbage collection, and provides a thread-safe singleton access pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods for session management.\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface methods\n- **GIVEN** a `Store` implementation (Redis or Valkey)\n- **WHEN** the interface is used\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide:\n  - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` - verify connectivity\n  - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - retrieve sandbox\n  - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - create new sandbox\n  - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - update existing sandbox\n  - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` - delete sandbox\n  - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list expired\n  - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list inactive\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` - update activity timestamp\n  - `Close() error` - close the store connection\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n- **AND** returns nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Ping fails on unhealthy server\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable or unhealthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when operations target a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` exists in the backend\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"unknown-session\")` is called\n- **THEN** the returned error SHALL be `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** the result SHALL be nil\n\n#### Scenario: Redis nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** a Redis backend\n- **AND** a non-existent session key\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `redis.Nil`\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey backend\n- **AND** a non-existent session key\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `IsValkeyNil` response\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Update activity on missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"missing-id\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify any ZSET indexes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Key Naming\n\nThe system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction for session\n- **GIVEN** a session id `abc123`\n- **WHEN** the store writes or reads sandbox data\n- **THEN** the string key SHALL be `session:abc123`\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction with special characters\n- **GIVEN** a session id containing special characters like `sess-123_test.abc`\n- **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n- **THEN** the key SHALL be `session:sess-123_test.abc`\n- **AND** the session id SHALL be preserved exactly\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Expiry Index Management\n\nThe system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds for garbage collection.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` and `ExpiresAt=time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n","exit":0,"description":"Verify delta-spec.md content","truncated":false},"title":"Verify delta-spec.md content","time":{"start":1775864619905,"end":1775864619933}}}}
