{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864648122,"sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","part":{"id":"prt_d79c7e68b001CnIO1dmRFdl2Mf","messageID":"msg_d79c7bf2a0011prSkJQ6OlGl55","sessionID":"ses_2863dceebffelqyTI39yZzng5G","type":"text","text":"The delta-spec.md file has been created successfully for AR-012 (Session Store Interface Definition). \n\n**Summary:**\n\n| Item | Count |\n|------|-------|\n| Total lines | 640 |\n| GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios | 58 |\n| Requirements covered | 13 |\n\n**Key sections covered:**\n\n1. **Store Interface Contract** - All 9 Store methods with Ping verification\n2. **Not Found Semantics** - Redis/Valkey nil handling, `ErrNotFound` translation\n3. **Session Key Naming** - `session:{id}` prefix patterns\n4. **Expiry Index Management** - ZSET operations for garbage collection\n5. **Last-Activity Index Management** - Activity tracking ZSETs\n6. **StoreSandbox Atomicity** - Pipeline operations, validation (nil, zero expiry)\n7. **UpdateSandbox Semantics** - SET XX behavior, no index modification\n8. **DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup** - Full removal pipeline\n9. **List Loaders Tolerance** - Orphan ZSET member handling\n10. **UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions** - Empty ID, zero time, existence checks\n11. **Provider Selection** - STORE_TYPE environment variable handling\n12. **Redis Environment** - REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD policies\n13. **Valkey Environment** - VALKEY_ADDR, optional flags (DisableCache, ForceSingleClient)\n14. **Singleton Access Pattern** - `sync.Once`, fatal logging on failure\n15. **Store Close Behavior** - Connection cleanup\n\nThe spec follows OpenSpec format with comprehensive GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios for both Redis and Valkey implementations.","time":{"start":1775864648120,"end":1775864648120}}}
